@{
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        ViewData["Title"] = @brand.TitleTag;
    }
}

@section MetaTags {
    @foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
    {
        <meta name="keywords" content="@brand.MetaKeywords" />
        <meta name="description" content="@brand.MetaDescription" />
    }
}
@foreach (var brand in ViewBag.Tag)
{
    <div class="m-t90">
        <h1 class="latest-bike-head">@brand.BrandName Bikes</h1>
            @*<h2 class="latest-bike-description p-b20">@brand.Discription</h2>*@
        <div class="brand-info-container">
            <div class="brand-info-content">

                <h3>TVS Bikes in India: Models, Price List, Mileage & More (2025)</h3>

                <p class="brand-info-short">
                    TVS Motor Company is one of India’s most trusted and innovative two-wheeler brands. With a legacy that stretches over four decades, TVS has earned a special place in the hearts of Indian riders—thanks to its consistent focus on quality, performance, affordability, and technology.

                    Whether you're looking for a reliable commuter motorcycle, a performance-oriented street machine, or a comfortable cruiser for weekend getaways, TVS offers a versatile lineup for every kind of rider. From the humble TVS Sport to the sporty Apache RR 310 and the modern-retro Ronin, TVS continues to make waves across urban, rural, and even international markets.

                    In this article, we’ll explore the latest TVS bikes in India for 2025, including pricing, mileage, touring options, and what makes the brand so popular.
                </p>
                <div class="brand-info-full" id="tvsMoreText">
                    <h3>TVS Bikes Price List 2025 in India</h3>
                    <p>
                        Here’s an updated list of the most popular TVS motorcycles, along with their ex-showroom prices and mileage figures:
                    </p>

                    <div class="brand-table-wrapper">
                        <table class="brand-info-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Model</th>
                                    <th>Ex-Showroom Price</th>
                                    <th>Mileage</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>

                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Sport</td>
                                    <td>₹60,000 – ₹70,000</td>
                                    <td>70–75 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Radeon</td>
                                    <td>₹72,000 – ₹80,000</td>
                                    <td>65–68 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Star City Plus</td>
                                    <td>₹75,000 – ₹82,000</td>
                                    <td>67–70 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Apache RTR 160 2V</td>
                                    <td>₹1.19 lakh – ₹1.25 lakh</td>
                                    <td>45–50 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Apache RTR 160 4V</td>
                                    <td>₹1.24 lakh – ₹1.30 lakh</td>
                                    <td>42–47 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Apache RTR 180</td>
                                    <td>₹1.32 lakh – ₹1.35 lakh</td>
                                    <td>40–45 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Apache RTR 200 4V</td>
                                    <td>₹1.50 lakh – ₹1.55 lakh</td>
                                    <td>35–40 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Ronin</td>
                                    <td>₹1.49 lakh – ₹1.69 lakh</td>
                                    <td>35–40 km/l</td>
                                </tr>

                                <tr>
                                    <td>TVS Apache RR 310</td>
                                    <td>₹2.72 lakh – ₹2.79 lakh</td>
                                    <td>30–35 km/l</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        <i>Note: Prices and mileage are indicative and may vary by city, riding style, and variant.</i>
                    </p>
                    <h3>Which TVS Is Best for Long Rides?</h3>

                    <p>
                        TVS motorcycles aren't just built for daily city commutes—they are increasingly being used
                        for weekend touring and long-distance adventures. The brand offers several motorcycles that
                        cater to highway riders who value comfort, performance, and reliability.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Top TVS Models for Long Rides:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Ronin</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Engineered with a relaxed, upright riding position and wide handlebars</li>
                                <li>Offers versatile performance with a torquey engine</li>
                                <li>Great for city rides that extend into highway cruising</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Apache RTR 200 4V</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Sporty handling, advanced ride modes, and Showa-tuned suspension</li>
                                <li>Ideal for riders who want agility with long-distance comfort</li>
                                <li>Dual-channel ABS ensures safer braking on varied terrains</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Apache RR 310</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The flagship sports tourer co-developed with BMW</li>
                                <li>Aerodynamic design, cushioned seating, and slipper clutch</li>
                                <li>Perfect for riders seeking high-speed performance with touring capability</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        If you're someone who enjoys weekend getaways or long road trips,
                        these motorcycles offer a balanced combination of comfort,
                        performance, control, and touring capability.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Which TVS Has the Best Mileage?</h3>

                    <p>
                        TVS is widely appreciated for producing fuel-efficient motorcycles that help reduce
                        daily commuting costs. If mileage is your top priority, TVS offers several excellent options
                        designed for affordability, reliability, and efficiency.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">TVS Mileage Kings:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Sport</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Claimed mileage: 70–75 km/l</li>
                                <li>Lightweight, durable, and budget-friendly</li>
                                <li>Perfect for students, delivery riders, and office commuters</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Star City Plus</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Claimed mileage: 67–70 km/l</li>
                                <li>Refined Ecothrust engine and comfortable seating</li>
                                <li>A great choice for riders wanting mileage with modern styling</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>TVS Radeon</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Claimed mileage: 65–68 km/l</li>
                                <li>Heavy-duty commuter styling with strong low-end torque</li>
                                <li>Performs well on city roads as well as semi-rural terrains</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        These motorcycles not only offer excellent fuel economy but also come with
                        low maintenance costs, making them ideal for everyday commuting and practical ownership.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Why Is TVS Famous?</h3>

                    <p>
                        TVS Motor Company is one of the most respected two-wheeler manufacturers in India.
                        Over the years, the company has evolved from a commuter-focused brand into a complete
                        motorcycle manufacturer offering scooters, performance motorcycles, electric vehicles,
                        and race-bred machines.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <strong class="brand-sub-heading">Key Reasons Why TVS is So Popular:</strong>
                    </p>

                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Wide Range of Bikes</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>From commuters to performance motorcycles and electric scooters, TVS caters to every category of Indian riders.</li>
                                @*<li>The brand offers products for students, commuters, touring enthusiasts, and performance-focused riders.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Racing Pedigree</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The Apache series was developed with insights from TVS Racing, one of the oldest racing teams in India. The result? Bikes that feel fast, sharp, and responsive. </li>
                                @*<li>This racing heritage results in motorcycles that feel sharp, responsive, and performance-oriented.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Affordable and Reliable</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>TVS products are known for their excellent value, low maintenance, and solid after-sales support. </li>
                                @*<li>Low maintenance costs and dependable after-sales service make them practical for daily ownership.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Innovation and Technology</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>TVS introduced India’s first connected scooter (NTorq 125) and is continuously innovating with ride modes, ABS, and app connectivity—even in budget bikes.</li>
                                @*<li>The company continues to innovate with ride modes, Bluetooth connectivity, ABS, and advanced rider features.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Global Presence</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>TVS exports to over 60 countries and has strategic partnerships (like with BMW Motorrad) to co-develop world-class bikes. </li>
                                @*<li>The brand also partners with companies like BMW Motorrad to co-develop premium motorcycles.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <strong>Strong Service Network</strong>
                            <ul>
                                <li>TVS has thousands of dealerships and service centers across India, ensuring easy support in both urban and rural areas.</li>
                                @*<li>This ensures convenient support for customers in both urban and rural regions.</li>*@
                            </ul>
                        </li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>Final Thoughts</h3>

                    <p>
                        TVS Motor Company is a name synonymous with trust, innovation, and efficiency. As we move into 2025, TVS continues to evolve by delivering feature-rich, stylish, and fuel-efficient motorcycles that cater to riders from every walk of life.
                        Whether you’re a commuter looking for unbeatable mileage, a student buying your first bike, or a rider looking for a reliable companion on the open road—TVS has something for you.
                    <p>
                        Their consistent quality, customer-first approach, and wide network ensure that you’re not just buying a two-wheeler—you’re buying confidence on two wheels.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Top 10 FAQs About TVS Bikes (2025)</h3>

                    <div class="faq-container">

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>1. Which TVS bike is best for daily commuting?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The TVS Sport and TVS Star City Plus are excellent options for daily commuters
                                because of their impressive mileage, comfortable seating, and affordable maintenance.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>2. Is the TVS Apache RR 310 good for touring?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes. The Apache RR 310 offers strong highway performance,
                                comfortable ergonomics, aerodynamic styling, and advanced rider technology,
                                making it suitable for long-distance touring.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>3. Which TVS bike gives the best mileage?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The TVS Sport is currently among the highest mileage motorcycles in the TVS lineup,
                                delivering up to 75 km/l under ideal riding conditions.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>4. Does TVS offer electric bikes or scooters?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes. TVS offers the TVS iQube electric scooter,
                                and the company is expected to expand its EV lineup in the coming years.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>5. What is the price range of TVS bikes in 2025?</h4>
                            <p>
                                TVS motorcycles start from around ₹60,000 for entry-level commuters
                                and go up to approximately ₹2.8 lakh for premium models like the Apache RR 310.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>6. Is TVS a reliable brand?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Absolutely. TVS motorcycles are known for their reliability,
                                smooth engine refinement, fuel efficiency, and cost-effective servicing.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>7. Which is the most powerful TVS bike?</h4>
                            <p>
                                The TVS Apache RR 310 is currently the most powerful motorcycle
                                in the company’s lineup.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>8. Are TVS bikes good for beginners?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes. Models like the TVS Sport, Radeon, and Star City Plus
                                are beginner-friendly because of their lightweight handling
                                and easy riding characteristics.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>9. What is TVS Racing?</h4>
                            <p>
                                TVS Racing is India’s oldest factory racing team and plays
                                a major role in shaping the performance and handling characteristics
                                of the Apache series motorcycles.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="faq-item">
                            <h4>10. Does TVS have scooters too?</h4>
                            <p>
                                Yes. Popular TVS scooters include the Jupiter,
                                NTorq 125, Zest, and the electric iQube.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <button class="brand-read-btn"
                        onclick="toggleBrandInfo('tvsMoreText', this)">
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script>function toggleBrandInfo(contentId, button) {

                const content = document.getElementById(contentId);

                if (content.style.display === "block") {

                    content.style.display = "none";
                    button.innerText = "Read More";

                } else {

                    content.style.display = "block";
                    button.innerText = "Read Less";
                }
            }</script>
    </div>
}
@await Html.PartialAsync("_BrandComponent")
@await Html.PartialAsync("_AllComponent")